<span id="freeTextContainer8370270676740420472">From the cover: Rachel Lyons and her partner Chase Cohen accept a contract to recover a lost priceless treasure in the Sea of Japan. However, upon arriving in Tokyo, they soon discover their mission is more complicated and dangerous than they originally believed. In order to prevent a natural disaster from striking Japan and killing millions, they must form an alliance with yakuza members, dive into shark-infested waters and recover three ancient cursed swords...before time runs out.<br/><br/>I received t</span>
  <span id="freeText8370270676740420472" style="display:none">From the cover: Rachel Lyons and her partner Chase Cohen accept a contract to recover a lost priceless treasure in the Sea of Japan. However, upon arriving in Tokyo, they soon discover their mission is more complicated and dangerous than they originally believed. In order to prevent a natural disaster from striking Japan and killing millions, they must form an alliance with yakuza members, dive into shark-infested waters and recover three ancient cursed swords...before time runs out.<br /><br />I received the book for free through Goodreads Giveaways.<br /><br />Even though I haven't read the first book in the series, I enjoyed this book to keep me reading – adventure, treasure hunting, romance, deaths and twists. <br />This book took place in Japan. The author must have spent time in Japan or researched about its customs, culture and scenery. I plan to find the first book in the series and read it. I look forward to other books in this series. <br /></span>
